commit 79cb4e4d216c9f6552dc15d2bb384f4d7d57d28b
Author: MichelKerkmeester <82775228+MichelKerkmeester@users.noreply.github.com>
Date:   Tue Jun 2 21:16:46 2026 +0200

    feat(132): make embedding resolveProvider local-first (Ollama > HF > OpenAI/Voyage)
    
    resolveProvider() was the only one of three provider-order definitions placing
    cloud above the local hf-local fallback in auto mode: when Ollama was down and a
    cloud API key was present, it silently selected OpenAI/Voyage — the opposite of
    the intended priority and the egress-conscious design (auto-select.ts cascade and
    getCascadeFallbackOrder() were already local-first).
    
    - resolveProvider(): drop the auto-mode VOYAGE/OPENAI branches; precedence is now
      explicit EMBEDDINGS_PROVIDER -> persisted-ollama -> hf-local. Cloud is opt-in
      (explicit) or reached only via the hard-failure cascade.
    - createEmbeddingsProvider(): add hf-local to the error-catch fallback trigger
      (not the warmup-soft-fail path) so a hard local failure cascades to cloud via
      getCascadeFallbackOrder('hf-local')=['openai','voyage'].
    - remove the now-dead isPlaceholderKey helper; correct the precedence docstring.
    - tests: rewrite the 3 legacy it.skip cloud-preference cases (T513-01b/c/d) to
      assert local-first and un-skip them.
    - fix two PRE-EXISTING stale active-ollama fixtures (createActiveNomicDb,
      createActiveOllamaDb) lacking the vec_memories_rowids table the source requires
      before honoring an active ollama embedder; surfaced by rebuilding shared/dist,
      confirmed pre-existing via a stash-and-rebuild isolation check.
    
    Gate: 6 embedder test files - 62 passed / 5 skipped / 0 failed (isolated DBs).
    Deploy: live daemon runs on persisted ollama; a recycle picks up the new
    shared/dist for the fallback path (deferred, batched with the 015 .cjs decision).
    
    Spec: .opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/132-embedding-provider-local-first
    
    Co-Authored-By: Claude Opus 4.8 (1M context) <noreply@anthropic.com>

