commit 138d2e932058443656d1b5c15da7a68c1a7ad77b
Author: MichelKerkmeester <82775228+MichelKerkmeester@users.noreply.github.com>
Date:   Mon May 18 22:21:55 2026 +0200

    feat(016/002/007): auto-embedder selection + purge llama-cpp surface
    
    Phase 007 replaces the hardcoded embeddinggemma-300m default with bootstrap auto-selection across a 4-tier precedence chain (Voyage → OpenAI → Ollama → hf-local) and physically purges the llama-cpp surface from system-spec-kit. Closes the operator-config requirement for fresh daemon starts.
    
    What was built (per codex implementation-summary):
    
    - shared/embeddings/auto-select.ts: bootstrap probes Voyage → OpenAI → Ollama (walking ADR-012 priority order: jina-v3 > nomic-v1.5 > bge-m3 > mxbai) → hf-local. Fails fast with clear diagnostic listing each tier probed when nothing is reachable.
    - ensureActiveEmbedder() wired into daemon bootstrap. Fills vec_metadata with active_embedder_name, active_embedder_dim, and active_embedder_provider on the first run when the table is empty.
    - Filesystem lock around auto-selection (mirrors the launcher PID-lease pattern from 006/007); prevents concurrent daemon starts from both writing the active pointer.
    - DEFAULT_ACTIVE_EMBEDDER replaced with {name: 'auto', dim: 0} sentinel. getActiveEmbedder() stays synchronous; the async network/Python probes only run at daemon bootstrap.
    - llama-cpp surface purged: shared/embeddings/llama-cpp-availability.ts deleted, LlamaCppProvider removed from factory, 'llama-cpp' removed from SUPPORTED_PROVIDERS, embeddinggemma-300m removed from registry MANIFESTS, node-llama-cpp removed from package.json, all llama-cpp tests deleted, install/migration scripts purged, doc mentions in INSTALL_GUIDE/ENV_REFERENCE/feature_catalog/manual_testing_playbook/references updated.
    - 8 new auto-selection tests: tier 1 (Voyage)/2 (OpenAI)/3 (Ollama)/4 (hf-local), fail-fast diagnostics, vec_metadata persistence, write-race serialization.
    - Architecture docs updated: references/memory/embedder_architecture.md, embedding_resilience.md, embedder-pluggability.md; spec-memory-stack CHANGELOG.
    
    Verification (per codex):
    - typecheck: PASS
    - vitest --run embedder-auto-selection: PASS, 8 tests
    - vitest --run embedder-ollama: PASS, 16 tests (regression check)
    - build: PASS (dist regenerated)
    - strict-validate 007: PASS
    - grep llama-cpp|node-llama-cpp|embeddinggemma|LlamaCppProvider under .opencode/skills/system-spec-kit/: EMPTY (purge complete)
    - Live daemon restart smoke: BLOCKED by sandbox process permissions (ps/kill EPERM on PID 4790) — operator does the restart manually post-commit
    
    Known limitations (per codex):
    - Live integration needs operator-side daemon restart of mk-spec-memory (PID 4790) to exercise the new bootstrap writer in vec_metadata.
    - Legacy artifacts NOT physically deleted (operator confirms post-restart):
      - .opencode/skills/system-spec-kit/mcp_server/database/context-index__llama-cpp__unsloth-embeddinggemma-300m-gguf__768__q8.sqlite (732M)
      - ~/.cache/huggingface/gguf/embeddinggemma-300m/{F32,BF16,Q8_0}.gguf (~2.0G total)
    - Existing jina DB has only 227 rows in vec_1024 (the embedder_set reindex job emb-swap-2026-05-18T19-38-28Z queued earlier hasn't fully populated; check embedder_status post-restart).
    
    136 files changed, +10041 -8203. Net massive simplification + smaller surface area.
    
    Co-Authored-By: Claude Opus 4.7 (1M context) <noreply@anthropic.com>
    Co-Authored-By: cli-codex gpt-5.5 xhigh <noreply@anthropic.com>

