Author: MichelKerkmeester <82775228+MichelKerkmeester@users.noreply.github.com>
Date:   Fri May 29 07:29:35 2026 +0200

    feat(spec-memory): consolidate local embeddings to nomic-only default (029/001)
    
    Make nomic-ai/nomic-embed-text-v1.5 the sole local default and remove every other
    local embedding model menu, while keeping a graceful runtime path for user-set
    unlisted models.
    
    - registry.ts MANIFESTS reduced to the single nomic entry (getCanonicalFallback
      still resolves nomic for ollama + hf-local via MANIFESTS[0])
    - factory.ts VALID_PROVIDER_DIMENSIONS local maps reduced to nomic-only (768)
    - REQ-003 graceful-unknown-model guard: a model absent from the registry, set via
      HF_EMBEDDINGS_MODEL/OLLAMA_EMBEDDINGS_MODEL, no longer hard-fails — hf-local
      resolveInitialDimension returns 0 / ollama synthesizes a dim:0 manifest, then the
      provider locks dim to the first vector length (per-vector assertion still guards
      corruption). Kept-nomic path resolves 768 via the map, not the fallback.
    - removed-model mentions trimmed from providers/profile/types + PREFIX_REGISTRY + docs
    - voyage/openai CLOUD_CANONICAL cloud providers + historical benchmarks UNTOUCHED
    - tests updated to nomic-only reality (registry count 1, dims [768], runtime-dim
      regression tests) incl. prefix-system.vitest.ts stragglers
    
    Implemented by cli-codex gpt-5.5(high,fast); 4-lens opus adversarial review
    (REQ-003 guard confirmed correct, kept path intact); orchestrator fixed the
    prefix-system stale tests. Verified: tsc (shared + mcp-server) + 79 embedding
    vitest pass / 0 fail; validate.sh --strict PASS.
    
    Spec: system-spec-kit/029-embedding-consolidation-hf-local-server/001-nomic-only-consolidation
    
