commit 312cca6e7ddd40ea74b7b7b68d313d3dab9d710d
Author: MichelKerkmeester <82775228+MichelKerkmeester@users.noreply.github.com>
Date:   Tue May 19 00:04:07 2026 +0200

    feat(016/002/009): byte-bounded profile-aware embedding cache
    
    Converts embedding_cache from count-bounded global (10k rows, no eviction in production) to byte-bounded, profile-keyed, task-keyed (document vs query). Closes the historical llama-cpp 30.7 MB + jina 19 MB stacking-across-profiles bug identified in deep-research-005 iter-010 Finding 4.
    
    What was built (per codex implementation-summary):
    
    - Schema migration: idempotent ALTER TABLE adds `profile_key TEXT NOT NULL DEFAULT ''` and `input_kind TEXT NOT NULL DEFAULT 'document'`. PK migrates from (content_hash, model_id, dimensions) to (content_hash, profile_key, input_kind, model_id, dimensions). Standard SQLite rename → CREATE → INSERT-SELECT → DROP. Idempotent via PRAGMA table_info() probe.
    - 4 new env vars (all generous defaults):
        SPECKIT_EMBED_CACHE_MAX_BYTES=100MB (global hard cap across profiles)
        SPECKIT_EMBED_CACHE_PROFILE_MAX_BYTES=50MB (per-profile)
        SPECKIT_QUERY_EMBED_CACHE_MAX_BYTES=25MB (input_kind='query' rows)
        SPECKIT_EMBED_CACHE_MAX_ENTRIES_PER_PROFILE=50000 (safety entry cap)
    - LRU byte-eviction via evictIfOverBudget(): tracks SUM(LENGTH(embedding_blob)+...) grouped by profile_key + input_kind; evicts oldest-touched first; calls db.pragma('shrink_memory') when ANY rows deleted (releases SQLite page cache back to OS).
    - embedding-pipeline document path now passes profile_key (active profile) + input_kind='document' on cache write.
    - Query-embedding cache wiring around vector-index-queries.ts:629-657: cache lookup with input_kind='query' before computing query embedding; cache miss → compute + store; cache hit → reuse.
    - memory_health full-report payload (from 008) now reflects REAL bytes via getByteEstimate() AND exposes embedding_cache_by_profile: { [profile_key]: { entries, bytes, by_kind: { document, query } } }.
    - Backward compat: legacy unscoped getEmbedding(content_hash, model_id, dim) still works (falls through to default profile_key='' + input_kind='document').
    
    Verification (per codex):
    - typecheck: PASS
    - vitest --run embedding-cache-byte-bounded: PASS, 1 file / 10 tests (migration, profile-keying, kind-keying, global eviction, per-profile eviction, query cap, pragma call, backward compat)
    - vitest --run embedding-cache: PASS, 2 files / 24 tests (existing regression)
    - build: PASS
    - strict-validate 009: PASS
    - Integration probe: inserted 60 MiB across 2 profiles, evicted to 49 rows / 51.4 MB, shrink_memory called 11 times
    - Alignment drift check: PASS (0 errors, 44 pre-existing warnings outside scope)
    
    Known limitations:
    - Legacy unscoped lookups are inherently ambiguous when multiple profiles share content/model/dim tuple. Scoped doc/query paths avoid the ambiguity; fallback is backward-compat-only.
    - Cache rows are recomputable. Rollback can clear embedding_cache if a migrated cache needs rebuilding.
    
    Co-Authored-By: Claude Opus 4.7 (1M context) <noreply@anthropic.com>
    Co-Authored-By: cli-codex gpt-5.5 high <noreply@anthropic.com>

